On a 32 bit machine:

  ./switch-target-distribution debian
  # Rename the directory if the output prompts you to.
  dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot -us -uc -I.git

  ./switch-target-distribution ubuntu
  # Rename the directory if the output prompts you to.
  dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot -us -uc -I.git

Similarly on a 64 bit machine.  scp the output in the directory above
to pacific and follow the instructions in simple-apt-repository-setup
